      "created_at": "2021-10-13T02:38:41.388Z",
      "cooked": "<p>This appears to be common to all training apps controlling a smart trainer\u2026</p>\n<p>See this article on Zwift Insider:</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/a256d12f61f0b2118b944982478fd121ac3ac9f1.jpeg\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"48\" height=\"48\">\n      <a href=\"https://zwiftinsider.com/erg-mode-in-zwift/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\" title=\"06:58PM - 11 May 2020\">Zwift Insider \u2013 11 May 20</a>\n  </header>\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/413;\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/0a91c9728d273df4870fd1be674e3b0c7073c19d_2_690x413.jpeg\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"690\" height=\"413\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/0a91c9728d273df4870fd1be674e3b0c7073c19d_2_690x413.jpeg, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/0a91c9728d273df4870fd1be674e3b0c7073c19d.jpeg 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/0a91c9728d273df4870fd1be674e3b0c7073c19d.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/0a91c9728d273df4870fd1be674e3b0c7073c19d_2_10x10.png\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://zwiftinsider.com/erg-mode-in-zwift/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">All About Erg Mode in Zwift - Zwift Insider</a></h3>\n\n<p>How it works, and when to use it.</p>\n\n  <p><span class=\"label1\">Est. reading time: 6 minutes</span>\n    </p>\n\n  </article>\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>I\u2019ve gotten used to it now, but if I get in trouble I turn off erg mode, shift up to a lower gear until I\u2019m at the right cadence and power before turning erg mode on again.</p>",
